mans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":39,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"William Holway was born in 1416, in England. He had at least 1 daughter with Cecilla Francis."},"et":{"1416–":"1416–Surnud","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1442–Female":"1442–Surnud","1416–Male":"1416–Surnud","1455":"1455","1442":"1442","1420":"1420","1470":"1470","1416":"1416","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"1416–":"1416–Kuollut","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1442–Female":"1442–Kuollut","1416–Male":"1416–Kuollut","1455":"1455","1442":"1442","1420":"1420","1470":"1470","1416":"1416","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"1416–":"1416–Décédé","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1442–Female":"1442–Décédée","1416–Male":"1416–Décédé","1455":"1455","1442":"1442","1420":"1420","1470":"1470","1416":"1416","England":"Angleterre","Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"William Holway est né en 1416, à Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Cecilla Francis."},"de":{"1416–":"1416–Verstorben","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1442–Female":"1442–Verstorben","1416–Male":"1416–Verstorben","1455":"1455","1442":"1442","1420":"1420","1470":"1470","1416":"1416","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, England","lifeSummary":"William Holway wurde 1416 in England geboren. Er hatte mit Cecilla Francis mindestens 1 T